This is so beautifully told for such a difficult situation. I lost my mom to breast cancer in July last year. It is so relatable hearing you say all these things... It is so difficult to show emotion these days in front of anyone let alone feel these emotions. My mom was also my best friend. And losing her to cancer left me with a lot of pain and questions . Can't imagine how she and other cancer patients go through this and then be our support structures and positive role models. Definitely takes a very strong and special type of person to do so.

This was difficult to watch through because I was crying the whole time, my mom was also a teacher and all of these stories hit home. So beautiful.

Thank you for sharing this journey with us. You are definitely not alone. May your family be blessed 🙏🌹 Sending love from South Africa

snippet.textDisplay: This is so amazing. I’ve been dealing with cancer since I was 15. It was leukemia for 2 and a half years. I’m not 3 years remission in that. When I was about to turn 19, I got diagnosed with thyroid cancer. It then spread to the lymph nodes. I’ve gone through radiation and it hasn’t helped. Seeing this has made me realize that I need to deal with my feelings. I hold everything in since I was 15 because I knew I had to be stronger for everyone else around me. Thank you Dolan Twins for helping me through this journey. I’m sorry for your loss. Your father in an angel above looking over you and your family. Much love and prayers.

Thank you Dolan Twins for helping me through this journey. I’m sorry for your loss. Your father in an angel above looking over you and your family. Much love and prayers.
